        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 6:04PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 604 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Mocksville, or near Harmony, moving northeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mocksville, Bermuda Run, Harmony, Turnersburg, Olin, Sheffield,
Farmington, and Cool Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
